    category: "Generative AI · Content Technology",
    status: "In Development",
    statusColor: "amber",
    year: "2024–2025",
    cover: null,
    headline: "AI that writes like you, not like everyone else",
    problem: `Generic AI writing tools produce generic content. Every brand ends up with the same tone, the same sentence structures, the same phrasing. Content teams spend as much time editing AI output as they would writing from scratch — and the result still doesn't sound like them.`,
    aiAngle: `Writeey is built on a core AI principle: personalisation at the model level, not the prompt level. Rather than asking users to write better prompts, the system builds a brand voice profile from approved content samples and uses that profile to condition every generation request. The AI learns what "your voice" sounds like.`,
