      "Scalable content production — teams produce more content without proportionally more people",
    ],
    snippets: [
      {
        label: "Voice profile extraction — learning what a brand sounds like",
        lang: "javascript",
        code: `// Writeey builds a voice profile from the brand's approved content
// This runs once on setup, then updates as users approve/reject drafts
async function buildVoiceProfile(approvedSamples) {
  const analysisPrompt = \`Analyse these content samples and extract:
    1. Tone descriptors (e.g. "direct but warm", "technical but accessible")
    2. Vocabulary patterns — words/phrases used frequently
    3. Words/phrases to avoid (identify from absence patterns)
    4. Sentence length and structure preferences
    5. How the brand addresses its audience (formal/informal, you/we/they)
    Return structured JSON only.\`;

  const profile = await ai.analyse({
    system: analysisPrompt,
    content: approvedSamples.map(s => s.body).join('\n---\n')
  });

  // Persist and version the profile
  // future generations will use this as their conditioning context
  return saveVoiceProfile(profile, { version: Date.now() });
}`,
      },
      {
        label: "Voice-conditioned generation — writing a draft that sounds like the brand",
        lang: "javascript",
        code: `async function generateDraft({ topic, format, userId }) {
  // Load the brand's learned voice profile
  const voiceProfile = await getVoiceProfile(userId);
  const recentApproved = await getApprovedSamples(userId, { limit: 3 });

  const system = \`You are a content writer for this brand.
    Voice profile: \${JSON.stringify(voiceProfile)}
    
    Write in this exact voice. Do not deviate.
    Below are 3 recently approved pieces — match their style:
    \${recentApproved.map(s => s.body).join('\n---\n')}\`;

  const draft = await ai.generate({ system, user: \`Write a \${format} about: \${topic}\` });

  // Score against voice profile before returning to user
  const consistencyScore = await scoreVoiceConsistency(draft, voiceProfile);

  if (consistencyScore < 0.75) {
    // Regenerate with stricter conditioning rather than show a weak draft
    return generateDraft({ topic, format, userId, strict: true });
  }

  return { draft, consistencyScore, status: 'PENDING_REVIEW' };
}`,
      }
    ],
    lessons: "The insight that changed the product: users don't want to write better prompts, they want the AI to already know what they need. Moving personalisation from the prompt layer to the model-conditioning layer was the architectural decision that made Writeey different.",
  },

